        "part_type": "Hadith",
        "path": "/books/man-la-yahduruhu-al-faqih:4:133:1",
        "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/1/132/5612",
        "text": [
          " : سَأَلْتُ أَبَا جَعْفَرٍ عَلَيْهِ اَلسَّلاَمُ عَنِ اِمْرَأَةٍ مَاتَتْ وَ تَرَكَتْ زَوْجَهَا وَ لاَ وَارِثَ لَهَا غَيْرُهُ قَالَ \"إِذَا لَمْ يَكُنْ غَيْرُهُ فَالْمَالُ لَهُ وَ اَلْمَرْأَةُ لَهَا اَلرُّبُعُ وَ مَا بَقِيَ فَلِلْإِمَامِ \"."
        ],
        "translations": {
          "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
            "Hadith.5612 - Mu'awiyah ibn Hakeem narrated from Ali ibn Al-Hasan ibn Zayd from Mushma'il from Abu Basir who said: I asked Abu Jafar Imam Muhammad ibn Ali Al-Baqir (as) about a woman who passed away and left behind her husband with no other heirs.\nImam (as) said: \"If there are no other heirs, the wealth belongs to him. For a woman, she receives one-fourth, and whatever remains belongs to the Imam (as).\""
          ]
        }
      },
      {
